                            <comment id="12866517" author="tsmets" created="Wed, 12 May 2010 09:09:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This file in pure UTF-8 encoding (Eclipse or jEdit) is converted into a property-file through an ANT-task (native2ascii) :&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;echo&amp;gt;Converting ...&amp;lt;/echo&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;native2ascii encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
                  src=&quot;${resources.dir}&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
                  dest=&quot;${build.dir}&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
                  includes=&quot;*&lt;b&gt;/&lt;/b&gt;.UTF8&quot; ext=&quot;.properties&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
                  description=&quot;Conversion the weird foreign characters into proper UTF-8 escaped characters&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;echo&amp;gt;Conversion done !&amp;lt;/echo&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12869900" author="bayard" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 06:48:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems odd. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Testing, the following passes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+    public void testLang623() &lt;/p&gt;
{
+        assertEquals(&quot;t&quot;, StringUtils.replaceChars(&quot;\u00DE&quot;, &apos;\u00DE&apos;, &apos;t&apos;));
+        assertEquals(&quot;t&quot;, StringUtils.replaceChars(&quot;\u00FE&quot;, &apos;\u00FE&apos;, &apos;t&apos;));
+    }

&lt;p&gt;So I think the issue is outside of StringUtils.replace. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Closing the issue, but please reopen if something is wrong with my test above.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12869902" author="joehni" created="Fri, 21 May 2010 07:19:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This test can only proof something if Thomas set the encoding option of the compiler to utf-8. Otherwise the test is simply wrong. Therefore it is always a bad idea to put non-ASCII characters directly into source.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
